
Overview of noun lark

The noun lark has 4 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                         
1. meadowlark, lark -- (North American songbirds having a yellow breast)
2. pipit, titlark, lark -- (a songbird that lives mainly on the ground in open country; has streaky brown plumage)
3. lark -- (any of numerous predominantly Old World birds noted for their singing)
4. escapade, lark -- (any carefree episode)

